  "description": "APPLICATION FOR A LAWFUL DEVELOPMENT CERTIFICATE IN RESPECT OF THE PROPOSED ERECTION OF A REAR ROOF EXTENSION, INSERTION OF 2X ROOFLIGHTS ON THE FRONT SLOPE AND 1X ROOFLIGHT ON THE REAR ROOF SLOPE. ",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - The operations comprising the erection of a rear roof dormer would consist of enlargement of the dwelling house within the meaning of Class B of Part 1 of Schedule 2 to the Town & Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 \"the Order\" and would comply with the development tolerances set out in said Class B. The operation would therefore have been granted planning permission by Article 3 of the Order. ",
    "Condition : 2 - The operations comprising the insertion of 2 rooflights on the front roof slope and 1 rooflight on the rear roof slope would consist of any other alteration to the roof of the dwelling house within the meaning of Class C of Part 1 of Schedule 2 to the Town & Country Planning (General Permitted Development) (England) Order 2015 \"the Order\" and would comply with the development tolerances set out in said Class C. The operation would therefore have been granted planning permission by Article 3 of the Order. ",
    "Condition : 3 - INFORMATIVE:  The applicant should be aware that the site may provide a useful habitat for swifts. Swifts are currently in decline in the UK and in order to encourage and improve the conservation of swifts the applicant is advised to consider the installation of swift nesting box/bricks on site. "
